He says that he plans to establish a chain acrobatics troupe and asks her to serve as leader. Velvet Touch feels very happy but Trapper knows that the master just makes an excuse to turn her away. Trapper is worried about Velvet Touch and decides to stay with her. The next morning, Velvet Touch gets up and finds that all the people have gone except Trapper. She is very sad and realizes that her master has abandoned her. Trapper consoles him and promises to assist her in the future days.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Velvet Touch and Trapper stop at Carrotown for a rest. At night, Trapper transforms himself into Mad Wolf. He goes to plough twelve thousand square meters of field and digs out lots of treasures, which help villagers get over the great drought. Velvet Touch hears about Mad Wolf’s chivalric story and admires him a lot. Just then, she sees Trapper sleeping outside the house covered with mud and starts complaining about him.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The annual dragon boat race is cancelled due to the upcoming flood but the dragon boats are still on the river. Most villagers go to reap the harvest and only a few people are trying to pull the boats onto the bank. The tea shop owner Mr. Ferret is very anxious and says that villagers will inevitably suffer great losses once the flood pours in and destroys the boats. After hearing the news, Trapper transforms himself into Mad Wolf again in the evening and begins to pull the boats ashore one by one.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Two watchmen tell the Kitchen God that Mad Wolf is well qualified to be a sacred animal, and then the Kitchen God flies to Carrotown to look for him. He comes across with many people but cannot find the right one. He walks into a teahouse and sees Trapper putting on a variety show. He talks to Trapper for a while and rules out the possibility of his being the right person he needs.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is taking a stroll around the Marsh when all of a sudden a giant “owl” falls from the sky. Fearing that the scary bird would devour him, Joe hides himself behind a big rock. Bartle Bee passes by and finds something wrong about this furious “owl”. After a close examination, he discovers that this is not a bird but a paper kite. To fly the kite, Joe slides down a slope to help the kite gain altitude. The kite soars into the sky, taking Joe along on an exciting flight. At first, the fact that he’s ten feet off the ground frightens Joe Croaker. But as he manages to keep the kite under control, he finds himself fascinated by the midair adventure. Joe flies his “glider” and snatches the cheese from Cosmo, which makes the latter really angry. Joe gets completely carried away, when the kite flies into a desert scattered with cacti and becomes out of hand. In the end, Joe crashes in a huge cactus with his “glider”.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is casting about desperately for something to fill his empty stomach. Luckily for him, he finds some biscuits in a large can. So he jumps right into the can and gobbles up all the biscuits. But after the feast, the frog finds himself unable to get out of the can with an overstuffed belly. He tries all sorts of avenues and finally manages to hop up to the top. Suddenly, the can starts to roll down a slope. Joe freaks out inside the running can and cries for help, which is heard by Cosmo and Bartle Bee who happen to play nearby. They attempt to put a stop to the crazy can, but to no avail. At last, the can is halted on the edge of a cliff. Just when the Bartle Bee and his friends think they are safe, a rock comes running down, knocking the can down into the river. Fortunately enough, the three of them are saved by a large lotus leaf.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee finds a flowering plant in the forest. It is so good-looking that when Bartle Bee leaves, Joe Croaker brings it home and plants it in his back yard. The frog loves the plant and does not allow anyone except himself to touch it. But Cosmo still gets a nimble off one flower petal and the fly becomes extremely aggressive. Cosmo beats Joe Croaker up and makes the frog do his chores and give him massage.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo finds a discarded solar-powered toy car in the bush. He decides to keep it as a desirable toy. He shows off his new acquisition to Joe Croaker, who is immediately taken with the car as well. Joe Croaker seizes the car from Cosmo and tries to tug it home. As noon comes, the solar-powered car harnesses enough energy from the sun and starts to run on its own. Joe Croaker ties the car to a little tree, trying to keep it still. But fully charged with solar energy, the car breaks free of the restraint and takes Joe Croaker on an exciting road trip. Though a bit scared, Joe gets off on this wild car adventure. He snatches Cosmo’s cheese on the way. The car runs wild again and plunges into a pond, drowning Joe Croaker as well. Cosmo catches up, only to find his cheese cake gone under water.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo spots a paper boat on the stream. He picks two fine leaves as paddles and begins to go around in his boat. Flutterby is interested in the boat and she asks if she can join Cosmo. Cosmo refuses and Flutterby decides to make one boat on her own. She selects a large leaf and bends it into a boat.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: A Whole New World & Bramble the Brave
programme.desc: Little Briar takes Vick’s axe and runs away with little Bramble. Vick follows them to the Pine Tree Kindergarten and meets many little animals there. Ms. Olivia tells him not to be afraid, and soon Vick gets along with the little animals there. Little Briar doesn’t want to join Vick and the other animals, seeming a bit lonely. Ms. Olivia then encourages little Briar to play with the others. At last, the kids at the kindergarten have a good time listening to Vick telling stories of the outside world.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Light Up, Little Guy & Happy Camping
programme.desc: The kids get in a cave of fireflies by chance, where they meet a firefly that can’t glow. They try to help it, but none of the methods work. Coach Mack tells them that a firefly takes in oxygen through air holes on its belly, and the more it takes in, the brighter the light it generates. By utilizing this principle, they encourage the little guy to light up at last.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: A Bear’s Gotta Do What A Bear’s Gotta Do & The Watermelon Patch
programme.desc: Young Little Bramble is dependent on his brother doing everything, otherwise he’s gonna cry. Little Briar loves his little brother so he always makes a compromise. He takes him to school, lets him have the bigger apple, and win the game. In math class, Little Bramble is required to answer questions by himself. He fails and bursts into tears. After school, Little Bramble, who’s eager to catch up with Briar, walks home alone and works out math questions all by himself. Now he understands what his brother says, a bear’s gotta do what a bear’s gotta do.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Be Our Guest & Grow Bramble Grow!
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble invite Hoo Hoo to their lair. In order to treat their guest the best they can, they offer Hoo Hoo the best things they have, which turns out to be a great torture to Hoo Hoo instead. Hoo Hoo can’t stand it anymore and even finds herself unable to fly. Luckily, Mama Bear arrives home and saves her. She tells her sons --- Walk in others’ shoes, and then you’ll know what they really want. Then they provide Hoo Hoo with what she really needs, and have a wonderful dinner together.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Coach Mack teaches the kids not to open the door to strangers at class, and the next day, he disguises as a stranger to test the bear brothers. Mama bear cooperates with Coach Mack on the test and leaves home. Coach Mack tries various means to get the bear brothers to open the door, but to no avail. At last, the bear brothers pass the test.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo and Tiki have a fight when they are playing with building blocks. They both storm off. Bramble tries to help them make peace with each other, and asks Miss Olivia for help. She prepares a special extracurricular activity for Tiki and Luna-Loo. They have to cooperate with each other to overcome obstacles and win the prize. When they finally get the prize, they realize the importance of teamwork.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: A Father’s Love & See the Signs
programme.desc: Babu is unhappy because his father doesn’t compliment him at Parents Day like the other parents. He thinks Barbara is very considerate when he’s learning paper cut in the bears’ house. Babu get blisters from the pair of scissors that is too big for his hand. When he gets home, he’s disappointed to find out his father doesn’t say much about his hand. He goes to take a nap while his father leaves home for work. When his friends come over to his home, however, they find out Babu’s dad have made many thoughtful gadgets for him. He even leaves a special pair of scissors especially made for Babu. Babu realizes that his father loves him in his own way.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo’s mom is going out for a trip. Her dad grows some flowers, intending to give her mom a surprise when she comes back. Luna-Loo wants to grow some flowers for her mom too, and gets a small lily from her father. She sees some wild flowers can grow very well without anyone tending them, so she decides not to take care of the orchid. The flower looks withered after just a few days. Luna-Loo realizes she needs to put in effort to gain something. She starts to take good care of the lily, which begins to grow well. At last she’s able to present her beautiful flowers to her mom when she comes back.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Ernie Jo’s Gifts & The Paper Boats
programme.desc: Ernie Jo makes a wooden vase, but only Tiki likes it. Ernie Jo is glad Tiki likes weird things just like him. So Ernie Jo gives Tiki a lot of gifts. However, Tiki doesn’t have enough room for those gifts, so he exchanges those gifts for bananas with his friends. Ernie Jo is very angry when he finds out what happens. Tiki realizes his mistake and exchange his gifts back. Ernie Jo the trouble he causes and forgives him. The cubs finally decide to share their gifts with one another.

But as he manages to keep the kite under control, he finds himself fascinated by the midair adventure. Joe flies his “glider” and snatches the cheese from Cosmo, which makes the latter really angry. Joe gets completely carried away, when the kite flies into a desert scattered with cacti and becomes out of hand. In the end, Joe crashes in a huge cactus with his “glider”.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is casting about desperately for something to fill his empty stomach. Luckily for him, he finds some biscuits in a large can. So he jumps right into the can and gobbles up all the biscuits. But after the feast, the frog finds himself unable to get out of the can with an overstuffed belly. He tries all sorts of avenues and finally manages to hop up to the top. Suddenly, the can starts to roll down a slope. Joe freaks out inside the running can and cries for help, which is heard by Cosmo and Bartle Bee who happen to play nearby. They attempt to put a stop to the crazy can, but to no avail. At last, the can is halted on the edge of a cliff. Just when the Bartle Bee and his friends think they are safe, a rock comes running down, knocking the can down into the river. Fortunately enough, the three of them are saved by a large lotus leaf.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee finds a flowering plant in the forest. It is so good-looking that when Bartle Bee leaves, Joe Croaker brings it home and plants it in his back yard. The frog loves the plant and does not allow anyone except himself to touch it. But Cosmo still gets a nimble off one flower petal and the fly becomes extremely aggressive. Cosmo beats Joe Croaker up and makes the frog do his chores and give him massage.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo finds a discarded solar-powered toy car in the bush. He decides to keep it as a desirable toy. He shows off his new acquisition to Joe Croaker, who is immediately taken with the car as well. Joe Croaker seizes the car from Cosmo and tries to tug it home. As noon comes, the solar-powered car harnesses enough energy from the sun and starts to run on its own. Joe Croaker ties the car to a little tree, trying to keep it still. But fully charged with solar energy, the car breaks free of the restraint and takes Joe Croaker on an exciting road trip. Though a bit scared, Joe gets off on this wild car adventure. He snatches Cosmo’s cheese on the way. The car runs wild again and plunges into a pond, drowning Joe Croaker as well. Cosmo catches up, only to find his cheese cake gone under water.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo spots a paper boat on the stream. He picks two fine leaves as paddles and begins to go around in his boat. Flutterby is interested in the boat and she asks if she can join Cosmo. Cosmo refuses and Flutterby decides to make one boat on her own. She selects a large leaf and bends it into a boat.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: A Whole New World & Bramble the Brave
programme.desc: Little Briar takes Vick’s axe and runs away with little Bramble. Vick follows them to the Pine Tree Kindergarten and meets many little animals there. Ms. Olivia tells him not to be afraid, and soon Vick gets along with the little animals there. Little Briar doesn’t want to join Vick and the other animals, seeming a bit lonely. Ms. Olivia then encourages little Briar to play with the others. At last, the kids at the kindergarten have a good time listening to Vick telling stories of the outside world.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Light Up, Little Guy & Happy Camping
programme.desc: The kids get in a cave of fireflies by chance, where they meet a firefly that can’t glow. They try to help it, but none of the methods work. Coach Mack tells them that a firefly takes in oxygen through air holes on its belly, and the more it takes in, the brighter the light it generates. By utilizing this principle, they encourage the little guy to light up at last.

programme.title: Moconomy - Economía y Finanzas
programme.desc: Moconomy muestra documentales sobre negocios y finanzas.

programme.title: Grjngo - Películas Del Oeste
programme.desc: Grjngo es la fuente de streaming más grande del mundo para las películas del oeste.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Need to Put some wood in your truck bed? Follow along as Stacey lays down the lumber on the custom bed of the Snowcat! Got a Gladiator and want to drop the top and get some fresh air? No problem, Our Gladiator build will show you just how quick and easy it is to install a full soft top. And for all you guys out there that like to shift your own gearz, Stacey talks single clutch versus dual disk clutches and which one you might want for your ride. It’s all here, this week on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: It’s hard to think about hot rods and not have a cool music track fill your mind. Hot guitar solos and spinnin’ tires just seem to go together! Without a doubt some of the most famous hot rod guitar work came from a guy by the name of Joe Maphis, who laid down the smoking guitar on Hot Rod Lincoln! Tag along as Stacey takes you on a different kind of barn find and documents the restoration of a one of a kind guitar-owned by the “King of the strings” himself, and a fitting tribute to his legacy. After that, we’ll add some much needed cargo space to our Gladiator build, and dig into the world of manual transmissions… so much… so little time!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Everybody knows that painting a project vehicle takes a whole lot of time and money. Follow Stacey as he revives a 40-year old paint job on the barn find Scrambler! You won’t believe how much life that old paint has left in it! And all it costs is an afternoon and some quality buffing compounds and equipment. It’ll make you think twice about repainting your project. After that, the Search and Rescue Gladiator build grows up with a lift from Skyjacker—this Jeep is starting to get serious now! We’ve also got tips, tricks and plenty more on GearZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: You never know who you’re going to run in to while they are in the middle of a restoration project. Stacey takes the crew “On the Road” to meet two gear heads who have had amazing careers in music and share a bond over a particular ’57 Chevy pickup. It’s a great story that you won’t want to miss. Back in our own garage, the Gladiator gets some tasty meats and a new set of wheels—And you know Stacey is gonna take those tires bigger! So, we better take a look at replacing those stock brakes as well. We’re loaded up with plenty of tips and tricks on GearZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Stunt Double Assembly - Bed, Bar & Beyond
programme.desc: We’re seeing double in the Gearz Garage! Stunt Double, that is. This amazing square body is coming together! Tag along as Stacey preps the bed with fender flairs, a roll bar and some blazing spotlights to keep that “Fall Guy” look with a modern twist. The front fenders are next, and you can really see this truck take shape! Then it’s on to the Gladiator build and we’re gonna light the place up and make sure our search and rescue rig can see in the dark. We’ve got tech advice and new products to show and it’s all right here on Gearz!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Square Body trucks are just about the hottest thing on the restoration market these days and our Stunt Double is no exception! But being a hot project isn’t the same as sweating in your cab or having your engine overheat, so tag along as Stacey upgrades the AC and the cooling system to make sure this square body stays cool under the hood and behind the steering wheel. And speaking of getting frosted… nothing kills your good time like returning to your Jeep and seeing that your stuff has been stolen! Stacey has a fix for that too. Follow along as the Gladiator build get some new security boxes. We’re keeping things cool on this episode of Gearz!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: It’s no coincidence that when you look at a vehicle you see a face. The headlights, bumper and grille are all key elements that add personality to each car and truck. Stacey shows how to layout and even change the face on your project by rolling in an ‘86 Chevy truck and showing all the parts and options available. It’s like a giant aftermarket parts buffet where you ultimately decide how you want your truck to look... and when the smoke clears, the Stunt Double ends up with a unique grille, bumper and headlight treatment. After that, we roll in the Gladiator Search and Rescue jeep to give it an INSANE audio and navigation upgrade, along with plenty of great tech pieces and cool new products to see as well.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: The Cheetah is back from paint! It’s not an illusion… you don’t need to adjust your television set the fastest cat on the planet is back! Stacey is going to tell you all about what it took to get this beautiful beast back in the Gearz garage. In case you get lost in the magnificent Blue Moon candy paint, Stacey will be able to find you with our Gladiator search and rescue build, as he ties the project in with S.A.R.D.U.S.—Search and Rescue Dogs of the United States. This episode is going to keep you howling at the moon!

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Rapper, radio, and ATL TV personality Darian “Big Tigger” Morgan invites Caffeine & Octane into his home. Cameras look past his collection of 500 Michael Jordan shoes to focus their lenses on a one-off motorcycle the 6–time NBA Champion gave to Tigger as a gift; A second to none, muscle car collection by one of the founders of Monster Energy gets toured by one of our hosts.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.sub-title: Beetles, Bugs, and Buses, Oh My!
programme.desc: Caffeine & Octane is known for having something for everyone. That reputation is tested when over 100 VW’s, on the lunatic fringe of automotive, rattled into an event. The annual VW Invasion has swarmed C&O, bringing with it Bugs, Beetles, Buses and more by a very dedicated VW fan base.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Caffeine & Octane goes old school with Psycho Deville singer and pin striper Walt Richards. Richards has less than a week to hand paint his signature flames on a way cool ’50 Mercury. An introduction to Retrofit Lighting’s trickle down technology - from cars to motorcycles - that will revolutionize how bikes will see and be seen.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Twenty-five years of hand building record-setting race cars is no easy task. But don’t tell that to Don Panoz who takes on Porsches and Ferraris with his laid back personality and a full-production facility that makes improvised versions of Americas V-8’s; Caffeine & Octane gets an exclusive look at an elusive man’s life long pursuit of everything Chevrolet.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.sub-title: The Wrap on the Most Beautiful Cars
programme.desc: Wayne Phears’ Jaguar E-Type was nothing more than a diamond in the rough before the mineral rights attorney took on the basket case. Caffeine & Octane brings viewers the story of how Phears’, through relentless research and determination, restored and reunited the #10 Jag that Enzo Ferrari called “the most beautiful car ever made”; Atlanta Wraps shows how wrapping Corvettes and Lamborghinis can color a car fast. Caffeine and Exotics is featured again to show off the coolest wraps Atlanta can supply.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Rickey and Bryan race outside of their comfort zones, each competing to find the raddest car collection. Rickey hangs out with classic racer, Ron Green, who shows him the ropes in the ultra light '83 Ralt RT5. Bryan visits a collection of 120 racing motorcycle owned by mechanic and racer Mike McConville. Mike takes Bryan motorcross racing in his backyard after showing off his high horsepowered car collection. Caffeine and Octane alongside Ron Green visit Atlanta's first Concours d'elegance to look at classic cars that have been perfectly maintained for decades.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: There is no better way to wrap up this season of Gearz than to put a wrap on our Search and Rescue Gladiator build. Over 13 episodes, 13 modifications were made to this Jeep to turn it into something ANY outdoors person would love, and Stacey takes us through the build one last time before we let this Gladiator leave the garage. But with every project that leaves, a new one finds its way in and a ‘73 Ford F250 holds plenty of promise as Stacey introduces the newest build… Blue Steel!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey digs into the mysteries of finding a good project vehicle. Because it’s not just about tools and techniques, sometimes you have to be part detective to read the clues that tell you about the history of the vehicle. After that, he walks through budget and how to decide what level of project you need to do. It’s like a car whispering master class from one of the best in the business, and you’re only gonna see it on Gearz!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Sometimes the biggest problems you face on a project are fixing someone else’s fixes! You know what I’m talking about. The modified vehicle you buy, only to find that the modifications weren’t done too well! Stacey takes on old ‘77 Jeep CJ5 and starts correcting some issues by dumping the old sagging suspension and replacing it with a new 4” lift and some new wheels and tires. If you’ve got an old vehicle that has been hacked on, there are some easy fixes to get it back on the road safely.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: There is nothing more comfortable than an old pair of Levi’s, unless it’s an old Jeep. Stacey shows how easy it is to update a classic, without losing the classic feel of the vehicle. The exhaust system, steering and brakes are all areas that our ‘77 Levi edition Jeep could benefit from, so Stacey takes it under the knife and shows that the only thing better than an old, faded pair of Levi’s jeans... is a faded Levi Edition CJ5 with the right upgrades to it. Far out man!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey takes a trip to the ‘Days Gone By’ Museum located just outside of Nashville. This place is awesome! From horse drawn carriages, to a DC3, to an enormous collection of tractors… so much of America’s manufacturing history is under one roof. It’s a wild ride through decades of mechanical achievements and a lesson to the younger generation of gearheads as to what the American spirit is capable of! There’s also a working garage where the owner specializes in building hot rods and the restoration of the vehicles you find in the museum. Speaking of restoration work, Stacey shares some tips on wiring that will help keep you sane when it comes time to rewire your project vehicle. Lots of history and plenty of practical advice on Gearz!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Today’s muscle cars are something else, from Hellcat engines to Boss 9’s, and the ever popular LS swap, there’s a lot of muscle under the hoods of custom and production vehicles. But these cars didn’t just show up with all that horsepower, no, there’s a long lineage of American muscle cars, and Stacey takes you on a tour of a new an old muscle. There’s something to be said about the drive of the American auto industry and how our country built the muscle car legacy.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Ray uncovers the infamous “Brawner Hawk” – from the Dean Van Lines team – that became the breakout car in the career of Mario Andretti. Ray enlists HOF mechanic Jim McGee to restore the vehicle and, along the way, discovers a replica with many of the car’s original parts. After an award winning stop at Concours Amelia Island, the car heads to the 100th running of Indy 500 where Mario Andretti himself gets behind the wheel.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Dale Earnhardt Jr. wants Ray to help restore an El Camino, except add on a Laguna front end. It’s not a typical restoration, but it’s certainly a NASCAR performance-worthy restoration. Ray and the team build the car and then, in a bit of gamesmanship, challenge Kyle Tucker, owner of Detroit Speed, to a series of races against his award winning Camaro. But as always, Ray has an ace up his sleeve in Al Unser, Jr. as his driver.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: In the late 60s, Camaros, Mustangs, and Corvettes roared to the forefront of the muscle car world. When Ray gets offered a spot in a vintage race featuring these cars, he’s propelled to dive into their history and afforded a chance to get behind the wheel at the Brickyard. But because it is a pro-am race, Ray pulls in a partner – none other than Bill Elliott, aka “Awesome Bill from Dawsonville.”

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Everyone has a car they fell in love with. Maybe it was the first? Maybe it was the hot rod the guy down the street owned? In Ray’s case, it was the ’58 Chevy he saw in the iconic coming of age car movie, American Graffiti. When Ray gets the chance to own the car after years and years of pursuit, he jumps on it. But restoring the car to its "movie state" proves to be a grueling task that goes way beyond a typical build. But when it's you first love, you can't let her down.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: The premiere episode features a dive into the influence cars had on culture of California. From road racing in the 1940’s to the inception of the iconic Woody wagon on the California beach scene, automobiles undoubtedly shaped the West Coast attitude. Ray talks to The Beach Boys frontman Mike Love and surfing icon Laird Hamilton for a glimpse into the cars that are so connected to surfing culture.

programme.title: Graveyard Carz
programme.desc: The Graveyard Ghouls return with the final assembly of the legendary General Lee which so happens to also be the official screen-used, record holding, freeway jump-car from the 2005 Dukes of Hazzard film.

programme.title: Graveyard Carz
programme.desc: Mark isolates himself in the machine-shop and begins the assembly of the 440 4BBL for the 1970 Plum Crazy Challenger previously owned by a former cast member.

programme.title: Graveyard Carz
programme.desc: It’s a delivery day at Graveyard Carz! We jump back and show you every moment in the restoration of our legendary, screen-used, record holding, General Lee from the 2005 Dukes of Hazzard film. It all builds to a reveal the Duke Boys would be proud of.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: The word is out that Caffeine & Octane is the ultimate scene and the place to be seen. Even after 12 hours of racing at the Petit Le Mans endurance race, Henry Ford III, the great grandson of Henry Ford the industrial magnate and current member of Ford’s Board of Directors, showed up to take in the sights, address the crowds, and sign a one of a kind Ford Shelby GT350R. The GT350R will hit the road with Operation Hope to encourage young people to study math and science through motorsports; Covert car counterfeiter, Chuck Beck looks for Ford’s approval on his own version of a muscled up Festiva. YouTuber ‘That Dude in Blue’ David Patterson joins Skip and Bryan to get a special look at the motor-based philanthropic outreach and amazing cars that come with it done by John Hope Bryant, friend of Caffeine and Octane.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.sub-title: Delta Wing Racer with a Vengeance
programme.desc: State-of-the-art engineering and passion projects take center stage on this edition of Caffeine & Octane. The revolutionary Delta Wing Racer turns on hot lap after hot lap at Road Atlanta, and driver Katherine Legge offers insight on how “less is more” when it comes to power to weight ratios; the dark world of a graffiti artist paints a picture of a car called Vengeance while the hosts share the eclectic hybrids of machines that make it to Caffeine and Octane with Vengance’s creator Totem.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: The Concours d'Elegance from Amelia Island: Featuring bomb-proof Conquest Knight XV, '69 Camaro Hagerty Fixer-Upper, and car-enthusiast John Oates.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Amelia Island's own Caffeine & Octane car show,: Featuring $2,000 Wrek Racing Truck, David Patterson's favorite C&O cars, a plastic Citroen Mehari, and much more.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Caffeine & Octane: North America's greatest car show

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.sub-title: Voices: Sport's Radio Legend, Mike Bell
programme.desc: C & O: North America's greatest car show

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Chances are, if you’ve pulled a car or truck out of a barn or a field or got a “steal” of a deal on craigslist, there’s going to be some metal work in your near future. Well, Stacey’s no different from the rest of us, and just to prove that he’s got a classic Jeep FC150 that needs some TLC in the metal department. Hang out with us as Stacey talks repair or new fabrication when facing dents, warps, and rust… and check out the nasty corner dent on the FC as Stacey explains how to read a dent and the many different techniques you can use to “Bump” some metal and pull that dent out. You won’t need a box full of tools either, a couple of different hammers and some on and off dolly work will have the sheet metal back in shape quicker than you thought.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Ever wonder what goes into making a supercar a supercar? Top speed? Names like Ferrari or Lamborghini? The price? The pedigree? It can be really confusing, and nobody can agree… but Stacey takes you on a tour of several supercars and tries to figure out what exactly does make a supercar a supercar? From Rolls, to Lambo, to Viper, to GT and even a vintage Pantera, we’ve got your supercar fix on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey dives deep into the exciting and unpredictable world of the automotive auctions, as we follow two potential sellers to Mecum. If you’ve ever thought about selling or buying a classic car or pickup truck at auction, you need to see this show! Can it be full of frenetic bidding and sky-high prices? Sure… but we show how to approach an auction as an enthusiast or a collector and the kind of mindset you need to play the auction game! From original Hemi Cuda’s, to Iconic racing vehicles, to average daily drivers, we run across them all and give you a front row seat to the hottest game in the automotive world today. Let the gavel fall!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Old Faded Levi is back in the shop on Gearz, as Stacey deals with the final upgrade that every old CJ jeep can benefit from… A GOOD TOP! Notorious for leaky seals and bad latches, original jeep soft tops are probably the reason there are so many rusty jeeps around today! Fortunately, Stacey has a solution with a new Bestop Supertop. After that we go thru a few misconceptions a person may have when they go to replace weatherstripping on their project. It’s all about keeping out the wind and water.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Quick, what’s a tribologist....or lubricity, or stiction? If you’re thinking STAR TREK,… you’re wrong! If you’re thinking oil…. You’re right, and you’re gonna learn all about those things today on How to make your oil live long & prosper After that, Stacey digs into the delicate topic of missing VIN tags, titles, and paperwork, and walks thru the steps and challenges to getting your project legal so you can drive it down the road. Only on GearZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: On this episode, Stacey leaves the garage to visit a local car builder and his son. What he finds is not only one, but two, great projects that bridge the generation gap and the differences between classic hot rod and a road-course tuner build. These two may not agree on everything when it comes to the cars they build and drive, but they can agree that time in the shop with each other is time well spent! Then hang around as Stacey takes us through the steps of getting a 1941 Ford Coupe running and why taking it for a spin right away is not always the best thing to do. Only on GearZ!

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Ray uncovers the secrets of America’s greatest racing sport in the foothills of North Carolina. When moonshiners were looking to outrun police officers, they would custom fit engines to race the back woods tracks. That sport eventually evolved into NASCAR and Ray talks to the early adopters of this national pastime.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Grammy-winning musician Marty Robbins lived a double life, flawlessly crossing between the glitz of the Grand Ole Opry and track at Talladega. One of few musicians to ever achieve success in both genres, Ray is determined to return Marty’s iconic 777 car to the race track travel back to the 60’s and 70’s.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Legendary drag racer Don “The Snake” Prudhomme proves he is no stranger to the thrill of racing rivalry. Prudhomme’s career and subsequent competition with driver Tom “The Mongoose” McEwan earned the pair an unforgettable imprint on American pop culture. Legions of kids in the 60’s and 70’s flocked to the shelves for Snake and Mongoose Matchbox cars which helped make drag racing an undisputable American pastime. Famed director Ron Howard makes an appearance to discuss the incredible stories hidden within the world of Formula 1 Racing, the topic of his latest, epic feature ‘Rush”.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Ray finds Buried Treasures in the form of two race cars that had been left almost completely untouched since the last time they were on a race track. One is found sitting in a barn with the other trapped in an old car hauler. Upon uncovering the cars, we find both have big stories to tell.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: A journey to Indianapolis unveils the winning car of the 1955 Indy 500 sits on the roof of an auto mechanic shop. More than 50 years after it’s magic at the track, prominent Indy mechanic/owner Chris Paulsen begins to restore the car and Ray talks about the evolution of America’s illustrious Indy 500.

programme.title: Hands On Crafts for Kids
programme.desc: Today's show is all about perspective or how we see objects in space. Perspective is the technique of representing three dimensional objects on a two dimensional space -- like drawing a house on a flat piece of paper. It's all a point of view from which we categorize or measure -- like a tree that gets smaller and smaller as we walk away from it. Our first example is an optical treasure box with geometric patterns. Next, build your own kaleidoscope. Add to your art journal -- how perspective makes buildings and other city scenes more realistic. Finally, make a lightweight ball with streamers and watch it fly through the air and learn about perspective.

programme.desc: Papa Smurf's worries make him break into a rash of worrywarts. The only way to relieve him of his bout of indecision-inducing disease is to have him rub the horn of a Wartmonger, a sloppy, slimy, stupid and brutal enemy of the Pussywillow Pixies...

programme.desc: Determined to fly over Smurf village to catch a Smurf to take to the Wizard's Convention, Gargamel invokes his Book of Spells to help him. A series of funny flying machine mishaps occur and Gargamel is once more the laughing stock of the Wizard's Convention.

programme.title: The Smurfs

programme.desc: Each morning, dew is deposited by water sprites on forest leaves. Wait till you see what happens when Scaredy Smurf gets hold of the dew-making magic wand...

programme.desc: Nobody believes Hefty Smurf when he says that he's seen a huge sea serpent in an old Scottish loch. And later, they don't believe he's seen the evil Gargamel in kilt and tam o' chanter!

programme.desc: This is the dramatic, moving story of the friendship between Smurfette and her pet mouse. A sad event reduces Smurfette to tears... Can the Smurfs comfort the despairing Smurfette?

programme.desc: When a drop of Papa Smurf's new potion spills on the Smurflings' adventure book, the fictional hero springs to life. The dashing Don Smurfo, willing to rid the Smurf of the evil Gargamel, gallantly captures him...

programme.desc: Jealous of the attention Vanity Smurf receives when he breaks his toe, Jokey Smurf feigns sickness in hopes of getting recognition. Unfortunately, his ploy turns against him and instead of loving care all he receives is the proverbial pound of curse.

programme.desc: Gargamel, the evil but incompetent wizard, tries to trick Esmeralda, the gypsy, into giving him a formula to catch the Smurfs. Of course the gypsy proves to be much smarter than Gargamel, and the Smurfs even more so.

programme.desc: The village of the Smurfs used to live without a clock. But now suddenly time becomes a precious commodity and Brainy Smurf designs a schedule to take advantage of the new Village clock... Can the Smurfs survive the attacks of time?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: African storytellers sometimes play on magical powers. Brainy Smurf pinches a storyteller's powder pouch, believing that now the Smurfs will listen to his stories, and they do!

programme.desc: The Village of the Smurfs is protected from intruders by a spell that makes it impossible for anyone to reach it if a Smurf does not lead them there. But this spell is going to lapse in a few hours and the evil wizard Gargamel is on the prowl.

programme.title: The Kaplowey Scroll
programme.desc: There is a terrifying magic word. When you direct the word at something or someone, you make it vanish into nothingness! Can the Smurfs undo its evil power before Gargamel gets hold of it?

programme.title: Master Scruple
programme.desc: Farmer Smurf is the reluctant master of a genie named Gourdy, whose enthusiasm for service is somewhat excessive. After yet another incident due to Gourdy's overzealousness, Farmer Smurf says something he shouldn't and Gourdy disappears. And guess who finds him? Well, it's Scruple, apprentice to the evil wizard Gargamel. And who should steal Gourdy from Scruple, if not Gargamel himself?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clumsy, wanting to be popular, steals one of Gargamel's magic spells but it backfires and turns him into a dragon. It takes all of the little blue people and Papa Smurf to sneak back to the wizard's castle to find the antidote that turns Clumsy back to his normal smurfy self.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs don't want to be pirates stealing gold from passing galleons. But they fall under the spell of the magic Clamulet and become the crew of Bluebeak the Parrot.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the emergency call rings, all the Smurfs in the Village drop what they are doing and run to hear the news. But when Vanity Smurf calls for an assembly so that the Smurfs can admire his new hat, it is too much. They send him on his way out of the village, and Vanity has the bad luck of meeting Lofty, the Elf, who suggests a horrible mud bath...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Once in a blue moon, as the legend goes, a baby Smurf is delivered to the Smurfs and everyone in the village becomes attached to the new arrival. But a mistake has been made and the stork returns to take the baby back. Grouchy and Smurfette have become so attached to the baby that the baby is returned.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A strange little imp who is a master at games challenges the Smurfs to a contest. He turns the Smurflings into rigid game pieces and forces Grouchy, who never wins at games, into playing for the Smurflings' lives. Grouchy gains confidence, makes the right move, and frees the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Brainy feels up to the occasion when he starts the recipe for cookies. He is sure to win the contest: he borrowed a recipe from Papa Smurf's Book of Magic. But a big surprise, and some nasty happenings, await poor Brainy... and the whole Village.

programme.title: Essence Of Brainy
programme.desc: Brainy Smurf is not the same anymore. He is polite, considerate, modest and calls every other Smurf Sir or Madame. All the Smurfs are worried that Brainy has lost all that makes his personality. They ought to be worried, for Brainy has been the victim of a system called an Essence Remover that Scruple, Gargamel's apprentice, uses... But Brainy's essence is coming back!

programme.title: Don Smurfo
programme.desc: Everyone has their own dreams. That of Smurfette is to meet the legendary Don Smurfo, the dashing, witty, swashbuckling hero of many an engrossing tale. The Smurfs shrug at this infatuation. But when a real-life Don Smurfo appears in the village and Smurfette snubs them all in favor of the bragging stranger, they take the matter a little more seriously.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Balthazar brings Denisa to Gargamel to baby-sit. But Gargamel loses Denisa in the wood and she and Sassette meet and become friends. Sassette and Denisa work together to free the Smurfs from Gargamel's stewpot, and prove you don't have to be big to be brave.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Habia Una Vez Una Luna Azul
programme.desc: Una noche de Luna Azulada, tal y como la leyenda decia, un bebe pitufo aparece en el pueblo, y todos acaban cogiendole carino. Pero todo ha sido un malentendido y la ciguena vuelve a por el bebe. Pintor y Grunon se han encarinado tanto con el bebe que la acaban devolviendoles el bebe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Sonador vera cumplido su deseo de ser un Astropitufo cuando Papa Pitufo le hechiza para quedarse dormido, transformando el paisaje y a los Pitufos en una fantasia galactica. Gargamel vigila de cerca las travesuras de los Pitufos desde su bola de cristal, pero el hechizo de Papa Pitufo tambien tiene efecto en el y le transporta hasta el centro de una tormenta.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La produccion teatral de los Pitufos "Pitufo Robin" se convierte en realidad con un actor real del legendario heroe.

programme.title: Pitufo Sobre Ruedas
programme.desc: Cada ano, todos los Pitufos recorren la larga senda hasta llegar a unos manantiales termales de ensueno. Sin embargo, este ano unicamente Abuelo Pitufo, Papa Pitufo y Pitufo Natural haran la caminata hasta ese lugar. Los demas Pitufos estan demasiado atareados (o son demasiado vagos) como para caminar. Entonces, Pitufo Carpintero llega con lo que el llama su pitufurgon personalizado. Ya no es necesario andar: basta con ir sobre ruedas hasta alli... Por supuesto, las cosas no seran tan sencillas como parecen.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En lugar de insistir con su poesia, ya que nota que ninguno de los Pitufos la escucha, Pitufo Poeta decide escribir un libro. Y acaba de encontrar el material perfecto: un libro en blanco con una hermosa cubierta en el que comienza a verter su imaginacion. Entonces, en la aldea comienzan a suceder cosas extranas...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Carpintero ha tenido una nueva y revolucionaria idea: una especie de carro que se mueve sobre railes y no requiere que los Pitufos tiren de el. Lo llama pitufitren y hace que la vida en la aldea resulte menos cansada... hasta que Gargamel lo descubre.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel llega a esta conclusion: si los Pitufos siempre consiguen ser mas listos que el es porque hay cientos de Pitufos, pero solo un Gargamel. Sin embargo, si ese unico Gargamel consiguiera aumentar cien veces su inteligencia con una pocion...

programme.title: Pituplicacion
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel crea una formula magica que duplica todo aquello que toca. Y...¡sorpresa! ¡Ahora hay seis Pitufos Filosofos! Esto provoca algunas situaciones interesantes en la aldea... ¡Y tambien en casa de Gargamel!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Unos lentes rosados llegan a manos de Pitufina y resultan ser un sucio truco de Gargamel.

programme.title: El Hombre De La Luna
programme.desc: Cansado y harto de que no le aprecien, el Hombre de la Luna deja su trabajo y se retira en la Tierra, en la Aldea Pitufa. La ausencia de la luna en cuarto creciente desata el caos en las costumbres de los Pitufos, y Madre Naturaleza y Padre Tiempo tambien se ven arrastrados por el embrollo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hay un premio para aquel Pitufo que tenga la mascota mas adorable. Bebe Pitufo acude con Carino Dorado, una mascota adorable y carinosa de la que todo el mundo se enamora. Sin embargo, esa mascota es una creacion del malvado mago Gargamel con la que pretende destruir a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el hada de las flores aparece en el pueblo de los Pitufos, todos se enamoran de su encanto e inteligencia. Y pronto se daran cuenta de que se convertira en una especie de mama pitufo para todos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuidar de los animales produce consecuencias inesperadas cuando los Pitufos deciden llevar a un bebe dinosaurio de vuelta a casa... ¡a su propia era! Este es el inicio de una serie de aventuras en las que recorreran el espacio y el tiempo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: La Primera Navidad De Bebe Pitufo
programme.desc: La ilusion de Navidad se ve frustrada cuando Chlorhydris hechiza a San Nicolas para que no pueda repartir felicidad en Navidad. Afortunadamente, Papa Pitufo y los demas pitufos consiguen romper el hechizo y devolver la Navidad a su bosque.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las preocupaciones de Papa Pitufo hacen que le salgan verrugas. La unica forma de librarle de esta enfermedad causada por la indecision es que frote el cuerno de uno de los Verrugosos, los desalinados, viscosos, estupidos y brutales enemigos de las haditas del Bosque de los Sauces...

programme.title: La Estrella De La Suerte De Pitufina
programme.desc: Pitufina ha elegido su estrella de los deseos de la suerte y sera suya para siempre... mientras formule deseos que no sean egoistas. Pero Pitufina, con sus malas elecciones a la hora de hacer deseos, provoca que la estrella caiga del cielo y Gargamel quiere hacerse con ella...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos llegan a la antigua Espana y el amable Papa Pitufo, que esta ocupado con un experimento crucial, pierde la paciencia. De hecho, la pierde materialmente... con resultados sorprendentes para todos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo se siente preparado para la ocasion cuando empieza a preparar una receta de galletas. Esta convencido de que va a ganar el concurso, ya que ha tomado prestada una receta del libro de magia de Papa Pitufo. Sin embargo, una gran sorpresa y algunas situaciones desagradables aguardan al pobre Pitufo Filosofo y a toda la aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel esta decidido a sobrevolar la Aldea Pitufa para atrapar a un Pitufo y llevarlo a la Convencion de los Magos, e invoca a su libro de hechizos para que le ayude. Esto da lugar a una serie de divertidos contratiempos con su maquina voladora, y Gargamel vuelve a convertirse en el hazme reir de la Convencion de los Magos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos aprenden que la mente es mas fuerte que la materia gracias a un enganoso y caro tonico milagroso de un charlatan. Pero Papa Pitufo les hara ver que no es mas que un charlatan.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hogatha se disfraza de premio de oro para observar a los Pitufos y capturarlos para sus ingredientes de belleza. Vanidoso acaba convenciendola de que pruebe su receta y acaba cubierta de barro de vuelta a casa de Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Es la primera Navidad de Pitufo Salvaje y esta impresionado por la decoracion de la Aldea Pitufa. Pero Abuelo Pitufo y Sasita van a ensenarle el autentico significado de la Navidad cuando ayudan a una pareja de ancianos a disfrutar de la Navidad mas hermosa que jamas hayan vivido...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Todos los Pitufos quieren un poema escrito para cada uno de ellos. Pitufo Poeta se siente superado por la presion y decide huir en busca de inspiracion. El rey Fiera Bestia captura a Pitufo Poeta y lo obliga a escribir un poema para animar a su hija. Pitufo Poeta descubre que la motivacion debe nacer del corazon, y nunca de la obligacion.

programme.title: Puro Trabajo Y Nada De Diversion
programme.desc: Los Pitufos malinterpretan las ordenes de Papa Pitufo de dedicar un dia de trabajo a los Pitufitos. En lugar de tomarse el dia libre, trabajan mas que nunca y se convierten en automatas. La unica cura para esta enfermedad es hacer que no piensen en el trabajo, algo que finalmente logran cuando tienen que rescatar a los Pitufitos de las arpias del agua.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un siniestro extrano aparece en la guarida de Gargamel. Es un cazador de recompensas. Por un modico precio, siempre consigue capturar a su presa. Y, si Gargamel le ofrece oro, ¡por supuesto que atrapara a los Pitufos!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada manana, los duendecillos del agua depositan rocio sobre las hojas del bosque. No imaginas todo lo que ocurrira cuando Pitufo Miedoso se transforme con la varita magica que crea las gotas de rocio...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Mientras intenta escabullirse de sus tareas, Pitufo Perezoso encuentra un antiguo pozo abandonado con una interesante peculiaridad: cualquier objeto que uno baje en el cubo regresa como nuevo. Pero ¿es eso bueno?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La nota que Papa Pitufo escribio avisando a los demas Pitufos para que vean un cometa esta rota. Al ser solo capaces de leer una parte, los Pitufos creen que es el fin del mundo. Todos planean como sera su ultimo dia, hasta que papa Pitufo regresa y clarifica el lio.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Gran Sueno De Papa Pitufo
programme.desc: El sabio y prudente Papa Pitufo, sin el cual el pequeno pueblo azul estaria indefenso, sufre la mordedura del Monstruo del Sueno en el antiguo Japon. Cae dormido y, para despertarle, los Pitufos emprenden un viaje...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos conocen a un elfo del bosque, que les ensena la lengua de signos despues de que Gargamel les administre una pocion de enmudecimiento.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una vez mas, el infalible plan de Gargamel para atrapar a los Pitufos ha fracasado. Los Pitufos aprovechan para gastarle una broma: disfrazados de pequenos angeles azules, le ensenaran a enmendar su conducta...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Esta vez, Gargamel se siente seguro de si mismo. Bueno, casi... ¡Esta a punto de atrapar a los pequenos Pitufos! Las ligerisimas tortitas de Pitufo Goloso casi provocan que los Pitufos floten hasta quedar al alcance de Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Mientras visitan Roma en la epoca de los cesares, Pitufo Pintor talla una heroica estatua de Pitufo Grunon que, como cabia esperar, la odia en cuanto la ve. Sin embargo, esta estatua es mucho mas de lo que parece a simple vista.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Perdidos en la Tierra de las Arenas Misticas, los Pitufos se encuentran con Ali Baba y su banda de ladrones montados en alfombras magicas, que roban las posesiones mas preciadas de los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos y Omnibus se hacen amigos de un desdichado joven cuyo maestro le obliga a robar. Pronto, el malvado ladron es entregado al magistrado y el joven esta encantado de irse a vivir con Omnibus.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Abuelo Pitufo llevaba algunos cientos de anos sin ver su antiguo juguete. Se lo entregaron a Papa Pitufo hace mucho tiempo y no recuerda exactamente como funciona. ¡Pero Bebe Pitufo sabe que tiene sorpresas para todos!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¡Pitufo Torpe ha desenterrado una extrana piedra! En ella, puede ver los eventos que van a suceder... ¡No obstante, conocer parte del futuro a veces trae mala suerte!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Caballo Anaranjado De Los Zapatos De Oro
programme.desc: Deslizandose por un arcoiris, un caballito alado pierde una herradura dorada. Tras encontrarse con Pitufina, ambos van en su busqueda. Al final, acaban encarinandose ya que quien podria resistirse al encanto de un caballito alado...o de Pitufina?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos aprenden que la mente es mas fuerte que la materia gracias a un enganoso y caro tonico milagroso de un charlatan. Pero Papa Pitufo les hara ver que no es mas que un charlatan.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado brujo Gargamel pide al mago Balthazar una receta para capturar a los pitufos. Implica secuestrar a la Madre Naturaleza para impedir la llegada de la Primavera. Por suerte, los pitufos salvan la situacion.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En la antigua Mesopotamia, despues de que Pitufina se pinche en el dedo con la espina de una flor magica, todo lo que toca se transforma en una planta. ¿Podra Papa Pitufo salvarla de las malvadas flores de Babilonia?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Nadie cree a Pitufo Fortachon cuando afirma que ha visto una gigantesca serpiente marina en un viejo lago escoces. Y, mas tarde, ¡tampoco le creen cuando dice que ha visto al malvado Gargamel vestido con kilt y gorro escoces!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Fortachon tiene un monton de cualidades: masculinidad, encanto, una sonrisa cautivadora y un bonito tatuaje en el brazo. Quiza eso es lo que provoca que una orangutana gigante de la jungla se enamore de el.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una aventura dramatica y conmovedora... Pitufina y su mascota Re chillido. La pequena Pitufina esta inundada en lagrimas. ¿Podran los demas pitufos consolarla?

programme.title: La Formula Aniquiladora
programme.desc: Existe una palabra magica aterradora. Cuando pronuncias esa palabra hacia algo o alguien, ¡haces que se desvanezca en la nada! ¿Podran los Pitufos anular su malvado poder antes de que Gargamel se apropie de ella?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En la antigua India, el perfido faquir Gargapuri vende a los Pitufos al raja para su zoo privado. Unicamente Abuelo Pitufo, Pitufo Salvaje y Pitufo Bromista quedan libres, asi que tendran que entrar a hurtadillas en el palacio para rescatar a sus amigos. Por el camino, liberan a todos los animales enjaulados de la coleccion del raja.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La Bruja Hogatha pierde su medallon magico en el bosque de los Pitufos y convence a Gargamel para que la ayude a encontrarlo. El malvado mago localiza el medallon.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado primo del Rey, Malcolm, lo ha convertido en un ciervo negro para poder acabar con el y ponerle en su sala de trofeos. Los Pitufos iran a ayudar a su amigo y, tras devolver al Rey a su verdadera forma, Malcom acabara preso dentro del cuerpo del ciervo negro.

programme.title: Los Amigos De Sonador
programme.desc: Cuando Pitufo Sonador decide visitar a sus amigos, los Tufos, Papa Pitufo crea una pocion para transformar a los Pitufos en criaturas de aspecto alienigena. Sin embargo, los efectos de la pocion desaparecen demasiado pronto y Pitufo Sonador tiene que enfrentarse a la realidad de que los Tufos no existen. Esta triste hasta que llega un alienigena de verdad para devolver a Pitufo Sonador su carta, ya que la recibio por error.

programme.title: Puro Trabajo Y Nada De Diversion
programme.desc: Los Pitufos malinterpretan las ordenes de Papa Pitufo de dedicar un dia de trabajo a los Pitufitos. En lugar de tomarse el dia libre, trabajan mas que nunca y se convierten en automatas. La unica cura para esta enfermedad es hacer que no piensen en el trabajo, algo que finalmente logran cuando tienen que rescatar a los Pitufitos de las arpias del agua.

programme.title: Que Suerte Tan Torpe
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren la supersticion cuando Pitufo Torpe rompe el espejo de Pitufo Vanidoso antes de una lluvia de meteoritos. Un meteorito cae sobre la casa de Pitufo Torpe y todos lo atribuyen a la mala suerte. Sin embargo, se dan cuenta de lo descabellado de ese pensamiento cuando comprueban que Pitufo Torpe no estaba dentro de casa en ese momento.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Sonador desea encontrar vida extraterrestre pero en la Aldea se burlan de el. Nadie le creera cuando les diga que ha hablado con un ser de otro planeta.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Otra estupenda produccion del teatro de los Pitufos basada en los personajes de Alejandro Dumas. Incluye algunas lineas de Romeo y Julieta. Una obra maestra de la escena.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Costal Magico De Santa Claus
programme.desc: Si hay algo que desagrada a la malvada hechicera Clorhidris es la bondad y el amor propios de la Navidad. Trama un plan para robar el costal magico de Santa Claus, en el que transporta todos los juguetes que los ninos que se han portado bien reciben por Navidad. Sin embargo, no sabe que un enfurrunado Pitufo Grunon esta escondido dentro del saco.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Tontin y Pitufina son capturados para ser exhibidos en una Feria. Papa Pitufo aprovecha la torpeza de Gargamel para rescatarlos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando los Pitufos llegan a las arenas rojas de Australia, Smoogle se encuentra con una tribu de sus ancestros. El y los Pitufos les ayudan a impedir que el malvado cazador Viejo Cindy los esclavice.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando una gota de la nueva pocion de Papa Pitufo cae en el libro de aventuras de los Pitufitos, el heroe de ficcion cobra vida. El intrepido Don Pitufo, que desea deshacer a los Pitufos del malvado Gargamel, lo captura con valentia...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Celoso por la atencion que recibe Pitufo Vanidoso cuando se rompe un dedo del pie, Pitufo Bromista finge estar enfermo con la esperanza de que le hagan caso. Desafortunadamente, su treta se vuelve en su contra y, en lugar de amorosos cuidados, todo lo que recibe es un proverbial merecido.

programme.title: Fortachon Y Pitufina
programme.desc: Pitufo Fortachon descubre lo que es estar incapacitado cuando se rompe la pierna. Pitufo Carpintero crea para el una pitufisilla de ruedas, un invento que le proporcionara algo de movilidad a Pitufo Fortachon. Pero, de repente, el malvado mago Gargamel aparece en escena.

programme.title: La Desgracia De Gargamel
programme.desc: Gargamel, el malvado e incompetente mago, intenta enganar a la gitana Esmeralda para que le de una formula para atrapar a los Pitufos. Por supuesto, la gitana demuestra ser mucho mas lista que Gargamel, y los Pitufos aun mas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Antes, en la Aldea Pitufa no habia reloj. Sin embargo, el tiempo se ha convertido de repente en algo precioso, y Pitufo Vanidoso elabora un plan para aprovecharse del nuevo reloj de la aldea. ¿Podran sobrevivir los Pitufos al ataque del tiempo?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel roba el reloj de arena de Padre Tiempo con la intencion de viajar al pasado y destruir a los Pitufos, a quienes culpa de que su vida sea un fracaso. Sus planes se ven frustrados cuando aparece Giganton y rompe el hechizo, que solo duraria mientras nadie viera a Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los cuentistas africanos en ocasiones utilizan polvos magicos. Pitufo Filosofo se hace con una de las bolsas de polvo de un cuentista, creyendo que con eso todos los Pitufos escucharan sus historias, ¡y lo hacen!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Debe ser por algo que ha comido. La gallina que ponia huevos pintados ahora pone huevos blancos corrientes. El escenario es la antigua Rusia, y el zar montara en colera si los Pitufos no encuentran una solucion.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando los Pitufos llegan a la antigua China, descubren que el emperador nino corre peligro de ser depuesto. ¿Y por quien? ¡Por el malvado Garg-Fu-Yun, que quiere hacerse con el trono del nino!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren el espiritu deportivo, la alegria y la amista cuando llevan a cabo sus primeros "Juegos Pitufos". Los Pitufos deciden ponerse en forma tras casi perder contra el gato Azrael.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Todos los Pitufos quieren un poema escrito para cada uno de ellos. Pitufo Poeta se siente superado por la presion y decide huir en busca de inspiracion. El rey Fiera Bestia captura a Pitufo Poeta y lo obliga a escribir un poema para animar a su hija. Pitufo Poeta descubre que la motivacion debe nacer del corazon, y nunca de la obligacion.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La Aldea Pitufa esta protegida de los intrusos gracias a un hechizo que impide que nadie pueda llegar hasta ella, salvo que un Pitufo le conduzca hasta alli. Sin embargo, el hechizo terminara en unas horas y el malvado mago Gargamel esta al acecho.

programme.title: La Formula Aniquiladora
programme.desc: Existe una palabra magica aterradora. Cuando pronuncias esa palabra hacia algo o alguien, ¡haces que se desvanezca en la nada! ¿Podran los Pitufos anular su malvado poder antes de que Gargamel se apropie de ella?

programme.title: El Amo Escrupulo
programme.desc: Pitufo Labrador es el reticente amo de un genio llamado Gourdy, cuyo entusiasmo por ser servicial es quiza algo excesivo. Tras un nuevo incidente provocado por el exceso de celo de Gourdy, Pitufo Labrador le dice algo que no deberia haber dicho y Gourdy desaparece. ¿Y a que no adivinas quien lo encuentra? En efecto: Escrupuloso, el aprendiz del malvado mago Gargamel. ¿Y quien podria arrebatar a Gourdy de las manos de Escrupuloso, sino el propio Gargamel?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Tontin, al querer ser el mas popular, roba uno de los hechizos de Gargamel, pero no lo usa bien y acaba convirtiendose en un dragon. Ahora tendran que juntarse todos los Pitufos junto con Papa Pitufo para colarse en el castillo de Gargamel y encontrar el antidoto que hara que Pitufo Tontin vuelva a su forma normal.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos no quieren ser bucaneros que roban oro de los galeones que pasan cerca de ellos. Sin embargo, caen bajo el hechizo de un amuleto magico y se convierten en la tripulacion del loro Picoazul.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando se produce una emergencia, todos los Pitufos de la aldea dejan lo que tienen entre manos y corren a oir las noticias. Pero que Pitufo Vanidoso convoque una asamblea para que los Pitufos puedan admirar su nuevo gorro es pasarse de la raya. Le echan de la aldea y Pitufo Vanidoso tiene la mala suerte de encontrarse con Lofty, el elfo, que le recomienda darse un horrible bano de fango...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Habia Una Vez Una Luna Azul
programme.desc: Una noche de Luna Azulada, tal y como la leyenda decia, un bebe pitufo aparece en el pueblo, y todos acaban cogiendole carino. Pero todo ha sido un malentendido y la ciguena vuelve a por el bebe. Pintor y Grunon se han encarinado tanto con el bebe que la acaban devolviendoles el bebe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un extrano diablillo, que es todo un maestro de los juegos, desafia a los Pitufos en una competicion. Transforma a los Pitufitos en rigidas piezas de ajedrez y obliga a Pitufo Grunon, que nunca gana a ningun juego, a jugar para salvar las vidas de los Pitufitos. Pitufo Grunon va sintiendose mas seguro, realiza el movimiento correcto y consigue liberar a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo se siente preparado para la ocasion cuando empieza a preparar una receta de galletas. Esta convencido de que va a ganar el concurso, ya que ha tomado prestada una receta del libro de magia de Papa Pitufo. Sin embargo, una gran sorpresa y algunas situaciones desagradables aguardan al pobre Pitufo Filosofo y a toda la aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo no parece el mismo. Es educado, considerado, modesto y trata con cortesia a los demas Pitufos. A todos los Pitufos les preocupa que Pitufo Filosofo haya perdido todos los rasgos que conforman su personalidad. Y hacen bien en estar preocupados, ya que Filosofo ha sido victima de un artefacto denominado removedor de esencias que Escrupuloso, el aprendiz de Gargamel, esta utilizando... ¡Pero conseguiran recuperar la esencia de Filosofo!

programme.title: Don Pituzorro
programme.desc: Todo el mundo tiene sus propios suenos. El de Pitufina es conocer al legendario Don Pituzorro, el gallardo, ingenioso e intrepido heroe de numerosas y cautivadoras aventuras. Los Pitufos no toman en serio ese encaprichamiento. Sin embargo, cuando un Don Pituzorro real aparece en la aldea y Pitufina les ignora en favor del jactancioso extrano, se toman el asunto algo mas en serio.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Baltasar lleva a Denisa con Gargamel para que este haga de canguro. Sin embargo, Gargamel pierde a Denisa en el bosque y esta se encuentra con Sasita y se hace amiga de ella. Sasita y Denisa colaboran para sacar a los Pitufos del caldero de Gargamel y demostrar que la valentia no es cuestion de tamano.

programme.title: DRAGON BLOOD -Sangre de dragón
programme.desc: Liu viaja a los Estados Unidos desde China en busca de sus familiares y la esperanza de encontrar una vida pacífica. Sin embargo, tiene en su poder un medallón de dragón sagrado que fue tomado de la corte Qing. Un asesino de Qing es enviado tras él, y pronto descubre que la vida en el Lejano Oeste no es nada divertida.

programme.title: RING of DEATH-El Puno Deslizante Sobre La Garra del Dragon
programme.desc: Nui (Cliff Lok) es un pueblerino con fuerza de sobra, pero con una ignorancia infantil del mundo. Tras dejar a su tía, que lo ha criado, busca a su padre en el pueblo de al lado, y allí le dicen que su padre es un sirviente de un célebre general. Los tres hijos del general y su profesor de artes marciales, así como uno de los hombres del general (interpretado por Dean Shek) hacen de Nui el blanco de las humillaciones, golpeándolo repetidamente. Al final, la bondad de Nui le lleva a la gracia de una pareja de kung fu hábil y pendenciera. Cada uno de ellos le enseña sus estilos (Dragón y Puente del Diablo) y él vuelve a la ciudad para dejar en ridículo a los que antes le despreciaban. Finalmente, en un combate de artes marciales con tintes políticos contra Hwang Jang-Lee, Nui tendrá la oportunidad de demostrar a todos de lo que es capaz.
